{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Fire Snake|kanji=丁巳|romaji=hinoto mi|onyomi=teishi|p=dīsì|w=ting-ssu|mi=tʰiŋ⁵³ sɨ|y=deng1 si6|j=deng1 si6|ci=tɛŋ siː|mc=tæŋ si|oc-bs=tæŋ si}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}

'''Yin Fire Snake also known as 丁巳''' (hinotomi, teika no mi, teishi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 54th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingchen|ja|丙辰}} and followed by {{ill|Wugo|ja|戊午}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Snake|ja|巳}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

==Yin Fire Snake (丁巳)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 57 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Teishi|ja|丁巳}}.
