'''Yin Fire Snake also known as 丁巳''' (hinotomi, teika no mi, teishi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 54th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingchen|ja|丙辰}} and followed by {{ill|Wugo|ja|戊午}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Snake|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

