It is the 54th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingchen|ja|丙辰|1=Yang Fire Dragon|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Wugo|ja|戊午|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Snake|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|1=比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|lt=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|qq=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|4=el|5=Ου Σιν|qq=draft|qq=draft}}).

